Lingua-Diversity version 0.07

This distribution provides a simple object-oriented interface for applying
various measures of diversity to text units. At present, it implements the
VOCD algorithm, the MTLD algorithm, and many variants of variety.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Lingua::Diversity

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Lingua-Diversity

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Lingua-Diversity

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Lingua-Diversity

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Lingua-Diversity/


